    "rationale": "All 13 V&V 40 credibility factors assessed. Twelve of thirteen factors meet or exceed required levels. The single gap (Test conditions, achieved 2 vs. required 3) is accepted on the basis that quasi-static rate independence of metallic pedicle screw constructs is well-established in the literature and the single-condition protocol is mandated by ASTM F1717. All three QoIs satisfy quantitative acceptance bounds (E/uval < 1.96; percent difference < 10%). The FEA modeling framework is deemed credible for the stated COU. Note: this package conforms to ProfileMinimal; digital signature is pending completion of the organizational signature workflow and will be appended prior to regulatory submission.",
